Palindrome Number

1. For python, change the integer to string than reverse it using x[::-1].
   Then only need to check if the reverse string is the same as the origianl one.
   
2. find the number of each place for an integer:
   ones place: num / 1 % 10
   tens place: num / 10 % 10
   hundreds place: num / 100 % 10
   ...
   
